                  <persName id="t18280110-140-person907">
                  BRIDGET 
                  COLEMAN
               <interp inst="t18280110-140-person907" type="surname" value="COLEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-140-person907" type="given" value="BRIDGET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-140-person907" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of John Coleman. On the 29th of December, I came into my room, and saw the prisoner there, about half-past six o'clock; I did not know her; I looked about, and missed my things - I asked if she took them; she said No; I asked her again - she still said No - I said if she would tell me where they were I would give her 6d.; she would not, but afterwards said she had taken them down; my little girl at last found them in the yard; I had seen them safe about two o'clock.</p>
